// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_Vil_SL4-5_Task_01 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2140777345" "Mangle is a poor, tortured creature - he doesn't know what he's doing!<br><br>Please, I'll give you anything you want - and I'll make sure to get the artifacts away from him. If you go in there and beat him down, it will only make things worse for everyone!<br><br>Mangle needs compassion, not anger!"
// Answer Text :
"P220390001" "You're barking up the wrong tree - now out of my way!"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P486845599" "You leave me no choice then, {HeroName}!"
// Answer Text :
"P260327663" "Hah!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Overdrive 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P3482909172" "The Compassion of Overdrive"
// DetailString :
"P1434614191" "You fought the heroine Overdrive deep beneath the caverns of Mangle's lair. She tried preaching to you that Mangle had to be saved, though all she was doing was getting in the way.<br><br>It is curious though that someone as weak as her was trying to meddle in your affairs - just why exactly does she seem so focused on saving Mangle?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Shards 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P1192730945" "Mangle's Shards"
// DetailString :
"P2349743556" "You found several shards within Mangle's chest, all belonging to that artifact. It's still a bit to go before you'll have the full artifact, but you're well on your way with these shards - and Mangle is back to square one, where he belongs."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P209407191" "Mangle may believe he has a place amongst the rest of the important people in the Rogue Isles, but that two-bit circus side-show attraction has another thing coming. There's no room for someone like him to try to step above his station, and you're just the person to show him why.<br><br>If Mangle thinks even for one second that he can send some two-bit thug to take <i>you</i> down, then he's got another thing coming. You're going to storm wherever he's hiding, beat him down, and then take any of the shards he's collected."
// AcceptString :
"P2416662853" "Bring the pain to Mangle!"
// SendOffString :
"P1103737946" "You have a pretty good idea where you can find Mangle's pathetic excuse for a lair. It'll be easy enough to burst in there and take whatever you want for yourself."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2872205804" "Take Mangle's shards for yourself!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1464397793" "If Mangle was smart, he'd leave his lair and just give you the shards - though that wouldn't be any fun at all, would it?"
// TaskTitle :
"P2573602545" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unearthly Shard</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Red><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2357471723" "You can hear the slow movements of slag golems echo in the caverns. It looks like Mangle has somehow gained control over them.<br><br>Not that they'll be able to stop you, of course."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1413215184" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unearthly Shard</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Red><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You step out of Mangle's lair and back into the somewhat sunny air of the Isles. All the shards in your possession suddenly glow, snapping together. You can see just how many shards remain to be collected before the artifact is fully formed.<br><br>Perhaps when you've acquired the full artifact, your first victim will be Mangle."

