// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2587945761" "It was easy enough to find out who exactly was helping the Scrapyarders organize this rally - the hero <color blue>Stalwart</color>.<br><br>It's simple to find where he's holed up in Sharkhead - Scrapyarders just love their warehouses. There's no telling what kind of annoyances this could cause if the Scrapyarders have a hero backing them. Today they're protesting Cage and Arachnos - tomorrow they could be getting in YOUR way. It's best to stop Stalwart here and now."
// AcceptString :
"P2016337200" "Kick Stalwart out of the Isles!"
// SendOffString :
"P3074715446" "You head off to take down Stalwart and his band of Scrapyarders. Why he thought this was a good idea is anyone's guess - but you'll show him just where exactly his misplaced heroics will get him."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2662334136" "Defeat Stalwart!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P2491916812" "Stalwart will never see this coming."
// TaskTitle :
"P726099960" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Nearby Sobbing Scrapyarder</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Red><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2540834337" "The warehouse smells of sweat and lost hopes. More so the former, but when you're done here the latter will fill the air."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P136442984" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Nearby Sobbing Scrapyarder</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Red><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You've kicked Stalwart out of the Isles, crushing whatever movement he was trying to start within the Scrapyarders. Hopefully that'll teach a lesson to any other heroes in Paragon who might be thinking about doing 'charity work' in the Isles."

